body:
Hello,
this is a side issue of issue #4514.
Sometimes, the __VForceRd signal does not show as public in the generated C++ code.
We do need it to correctly implement the "signal_deposit" keyword.
I have noticed that one line is missing in V3Force.cpp:
```
    void visit(AstVarScope* nodep) override {
        // If this signal is marked externally forceable, create the public force signals
        if (nodep->varp()->isForceable()) {
            const ForceComponentsVarScope& fc = getForceComponents(nodep);
            fc.m_rdVscp->varp()->sigPublic(true); <=== HERE
            fc.m_enVscp->varp()->sigPublic(true);
            fc.m_valVscp->varp()->sigPublic(true);
        }
    }

```
Can it be added ?
Regards,
Frédéric REQUIN

